2 New
*****

Five shades of grey characters can now be inserted in the same ways as
arrows, squares, circles, and crosses characters.

   тАШтЦСтЦТтЦУтЦИтАЩ

   See *note Intersection glyphs тЦа тЧЖ тЧП::.

   Note that those 5 shades of grey were already available to fill a
rectangle or an arbitrary shape.  They are now also available as
individual characters, useful for instance as lines intersections.  The
key-bindings are the same as for filling: space & back-space.

   Those grey characters are well supported by the recommended fonts
(see *note Which fonts?::).


