5 The тАШ<insert>тАЩ key
********************

The тАШ<insert>тАЩ key is a prefix for other keys:
   тАв for drawing arrows, squares, crosses, o-shapes glyphs,
   тАв for handling rectangles,
   тАв for inserting тАШ# = - +тАЩ which otherwise change the brush style,
   тАв for trying a choice of mono-spaced fonts.

   Why тАШ<insert>тАЩ?  Because:
   тАв тАШUnilineтАЩ tries to leave their original meaning to as many keys as
     possible,
   тАв the standard meaning of тАШ<insert>тАЩ is to toggle the
     тАШoverwrite-modeтАЩ; but тАШUnilineтАЩ is already in тАШoverwrite-modeтАЩ, and
     de-activating overwrite would break тАШUnilineтАЩ.

   So preempting тАШ<insert>тАЩ does not sacrifice anything.

   *Customization*

   Another key may be defined instead of тАШ<insert>тАЩ.  Type:

     M-x customize-variable uniline-key-insert


