   Actually, there are tons of arrows of all styles in the UNICODE
standard.  Unfortunately, support by fonts is weak.  So тАШUnilineтАЩ
restrains itself to those six safe arrows.

   To insert an arrow, type: тАШ<insert> aтАЩ or тАШ<insert> a aтАЩ or тАШ<insert>
a a aтАЩ.  (тАШaтАЩ cycles through the 6 styles, тАШAтАЩ cycles backward).

   тАШ<insert> 4 aтАЩ is equivalent to тАШ<insert> a a a aтАЩ, which is also
equivalent to тАШ<insert> A A AтАЩ.  Those 3 shortcuts insert an arrow of
this style: тАШтЦ╡тЦ╣тЦ┐тЧГтАЩ.  The actual direction where the arrow points follows
the last movement of the cursor.

   To change the direction of the arrow, use shift-arrow, for example:
тАШS-<up>тАЩ will change from тАШтЖТтАЩ to тАШтЖСтАЩ.


