7.3 Moving a rectangular region
===============================

Select a region, then press тАШ<insert>тАЩ.

   Use arrow keys to move the rectangle around.  A numeric prefix may be
used to move the rectangle that many characters.
   тАв Under тАШHydraтАЩ, be sure to specify the numeric prefix with just
     digits, without the тАШAltтАЩ key.  Typing тАШ15 <left>тАЩ moves the
     rectangle 15 characters to the left.  тАШM-15 <left>тАЩ does not work.
   тАв Under тАШTransientтАЩ, use the тАШAltтАЩ key, like anywhere else in
     тАШEmacsтАЩ.  Type тАШM-15 <left>тАЩ to move the selected rectangle 15
     characters to the left.

   Press тАШqтАЩ, тАШ<return>тАЩ, or тАШC-gтАЩ to stop moving the rectangle.

   The тАШC-_тАЩ key may also be used to undo the previous movements, even
though the selection is still active.



