8.1 Tracing a contour
=====================



       тХнтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтХо
     тХнтФАтХпA.written.textтХ░тФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтХо
     тФВoutlined by the.`contour'тФВ
     тХ░тФАтХоfunction.getsтХ╢тФмтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтХп
       тХ░тХоa.surroundingтХ░тФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтХо
        тХ░тФАтХоline.in.the.currentтФВ
          тХ░тФАтХоbrush.styleтХнтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтХп
            тХ░тФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтХп

   Choose or change the brush style with any of тАШ-,+,=_,#,<delete>тАЩ.
Put the cursor anywhere on the shape or outside but touching it.  Then
type:

   тАШ<insert> cтАЩ

   A contour line is traced (or erased if brush style is тАШ<delete>тАЩ)
around the contiguous shape close to the cursor.

   When hitting capital letter: тАШ<insert> S-CтАЩ the contour is
overwritten.  This means that if there was already a different style of
line on the contour path, it is overwritten.

   The shape is distinguished because it floats in a blank characters
ocean.  For the shake of the contour function, blank characters are
those containing lines as drawn by тАШUnilineтАЩ (including true blank
characters).  Locations outside the buffer are also considered blank.

   The algorithm has an upper limit of тАШ10000тАЩ steps.  This avoids an
infinite loop in which the algorithm may end up in some rare cases.  One
of those cases is when the contour crosses a new-page character,
displayed by тАШEmacsтАЩ as тАШ^LтАЩ.  тАШ10000тАЩ steps require a fraction of a
second to run.  For shapes really huge, you may launch the contour
command once again, at the point where the previous run ended.

   This тАШ10000тАЩ steps limit is customizable.  Type:

     M-x customize-variable uniline-contour-max-steps


