11.3 One-liner menus
====================

The multi-lines menus in Hydra and Transient are quite useful for casual
users.  For seasoned users, those huge textual menus may distract them
from their workflow.

   It is now possible to switch to less distracting textual menus.  They
are displayed in the echo-area on a single line.

   To do so, type:
   тАв тАШC-tтАЩ within a sub-mode (glyph insertion mode, rectangle handling,
     etc.)
   тАв тАШC-h TABтАЩ at the top-level.

   This will flip between the two sizes of textual menus.  It also
affects the welcome message, the one displayed when entering the
тАШUnilineтАЩ minor mode.

   The current size is controlled by the тАШuniline-hint-styleтАЩ variable:
   тАв тАШtтАЩ for full fledged messages over several lines
   тАв тАШ1тАЩ for one-liner messages
   тАв тАШ0тАЩ for no message at all

   The variable is "buffer-local", which means that it can take distinct
values on distinct buffers.

   Its default value can be customized and saved for future sessions:

   тАШM-x customize-variable uniline-hint-styleтАЩ

   After customization it can be changed later, on a buffer per buffer
basis, with the тАШC-tтАЩ or тАШC-h TABтАЩ keys.

   Transient natively offers a similar setting: тАШtransient-show-popupтАЩ.
(There is no such variable in Hydra).  It can be customized with тАШtтАЩ,
тАШnilтАЩ, тАШ0тАЩ (zero), or a number.  This is similar but not exactly the
same as the Hydra behavior and the тАШuniline-hint-styleтАЩ.  the Transient
setting stays in effect until the тАШC-tтАЩ or тАШC-h TABтАЩ keys are not used,
.  As soon as one of those keys is invoked, тАШtransient-show-popupтАЩ is
toggled (which does not happens in Transient alone).  The change is kept
in effect throughout the тАШUnilineтАЩ session, but no longer.


