12.2 Insert key
===============

By default, the тАШ<insert>тАЩ or тАШINSтАЩ key is the prefix for most of the
тАШUnilineтАЩ actions.  Some computers do not have an тАШINSтАЩ key, or it is
bound to some other command (Apple?).

   This can be changed temporarily or permanently.  The customization
allows to set several keys at the same time.

   Depending on whether тАШEmacsтАЩ is run in a graphical environment or a
text-only terminal, either the тАШ<insert>тАЩ or the тАШ<insertchar>тАЩ events
are generated by the тАШINSтАЩ key.  Therefore, by default тАШUnilineтАЩ defines
both events as the тАШINSтАЩ key.

   Variable тАШuniline-key-insertтАЩ.


