13.2 Compatibility with Picture-mode
====================================

тАШPicture-modeтАЩ and тАШuniline-modeтАЩ are compatible.  Their features
overlap somehow:
   тАв Both implement an unlimited buffer in east and south directions.
   тАв Both visually truncate long lines (actual text is not truncated).
   тАв Both set the overwrite mode (тАШuniline-modeтАЩ activates
     тАШoverwrite-modeтАЩ, while тАШpicture-modeтАЩ re-implements it)
   тАв Both are able to draw rectangles (тАШuniline-modeтАЩ in UNICODE,
     тАШpicture-modeтАЩ in ASCII), copy and yank them.

   They also have features unique to each:
   тАв тАШPicture-modeтАЩ writes in 8 possible directions
   тАв тАШPicture-modeтАЩ handles TAB stops
   тАв тАШUniline-modeтАЩ draws lines and arrows


File: uniline.info,  Node: Compatibility with Artist-mode,  Next: Compatibility with Whitespace-mode,  Prev: Compatibility with Picture-mode,  Up: How Uniline behaves with its environment?

13.3 Compatibility with Artist-mode
===================================

тАШArtist-modeтАЩ and тАШuniline-modeтАЩ are mostly incompatible.  This is
because тАШartist-modeтАЩ preempts the arrow keys, which give access to a
large part of тАШuniline-modeтАЩ features.

   However, it is possible to use both one after the other.


File: uniline.info,  Node: Compatibility with Whitespace-mode,  Next: Compatibility with Org Mode,  Prev: Compatibility with Artist-mode,  Up: How Uniline behaves with its environment?

13.4 Compatibility with Whitespace-mode
=======================================

тАШWhitespace-modeтАЩ and тАШuniline-modeтАЩ are mostly compatible.

   Why activate тАШwhitespace-modeтАЩ while in тАШuniline-modeтАЩ?  Because
тАШUnilineтАЩ creates a lot of white-spaces to implement an infinite buffer.
And it is funny to look at this activity.

   To make тАШuniline-modeтАЩ and тАШwhitespace-modeтАЩ fully compatible,
disable the newline visualization:

   тАв тАШM-x customize-variable whitespace-styleтАЩ
   тАв uncheck тАШ(Mark) NEWLINEsтАЩ

   This is due to a glitch in тАШmove-to-columnтАЩ when a visual property is
attached to newlines.  And тАШuniline-modeтАЩ makes heavy use of
тАШmove-to-columnтАЩ.


File: uniline.info,  Node: Compatibility with Org Mode,  Next: Org Mode and LaTex,  Prev: Compatibility with Whitespace-mode,  Up: How Uniline behaves with its environment?

13.5 Compatibility with Org Mode
================================

You may want to customize the shift extension mode in тАШOrg ModeтАЩ.  This
is because тАШOrg ModeтАЩ preempts тАШshift-select-modeтАЩ for other useful
purposes.  Just type:

     M-x customize-variable org-support-shift-select

   and choose "when outside special context", which sets it to тАШtтАЩ.

   You then get the shift-selection from тАШOrg ModeтАЩ, not from тАШUnilineтАЩ.
The difference is that the тАШUnilineтАЩтАЩs one handles the infinite-ness of
the buffer.

   Other than that, тАШUnilineтАЩ is compatible with тАШOrg ModeтАЩ

   Thanks to jdtsmith (GitHub) for sharing a funny fact he discovered.
If a source block is created with the тАШUnilineтАЩ language (тАШUnilineтАЩ is
*not* a language like тАШC++,тАЩ тАШPythonтАЩ, or тАШBashтАЩ), then it can be edited
(тАШM-x org-edit-specialтАЩ) with тАШuniline-modeтАЩ automatically activated.



     #+begin_src uniline
     тХнтФАтФАтФАтХо   тХнтФАтФАтФАтХо
     тФВ тХ╖ тХ░тФАтФАтФАтХп тХ╖ тФВ
     тФВ тХ░тФА    тХ╢тФАтХп тФВ
     тХ░тХо тЧП     тЧП тХнтХп
      тФВ      тХ╖  тФВ
      тХ░тХо тФАтФАтФАтФАтХп тХнтХп
       тХ░тФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтФАтХп
     #+end_src


