14.3 Example: Lisp function to draw a plus sign
===============================================

For instance, if we want to create a function to draw a "plus" sign, we
can code it as follows:

     (defun uniline-draw-plus ()
       (interactive)
       (uniline-write-riтЖТ 1)
       (uniline-write-dwтЖУ 1)
       (uniline-write-riтЖТ 1)
       (uniline-write-dwтЖУ 1)
       (uniline-write-lfтЖР 1)
       (uniline-write-dwтЖУ 1)
       (uniline-write-lfтЖР 1)
       (uniline-write-upтЖС 1)
       (uniline-write-lfтЖР 1)
       (uniline-write-upтЖС 1)
       (uniline-write-riтЖТ 1)
       (uniline-write-upтЖС 1))

   Calling тАШM-x uniline-draw-plusтАЩ will result in this nice little
plus-shape:



      тХнтХо
     тХнтХптХ░тХо
     тХ░тХотХнтХп
      тХ░тХп
     generated by
     M-x uniline-draw-plus

   We may modify the function to accept the size of the shape as a
parameter:

     (defun uniline-draw-plus (size)
       (interactive "Nsize? ")
       (uniline-write-riтЖТ size)
       (uniline-write-dwтЖУ size)
       (uniline-write-riтЖТ size)
       (uniline-write-dwтЖУ size)
       (uniline-write-lfтЖР size)
       (uniline-write-dwтЖУ size)
       (uniline-write-lfтЖР size)
       (uniline-write-upтЖС size)
       (uniline-write-lfтЖР size)
       (uniline-write-upтЖС size)
       (uniline-write-riтЖТ size)
       (uniline-write-upтЖС size))

   The тАШ(interactive "Nsize? ")тАЩ form prompts user for the size of the
shape if not given as a parameter.

   This API works in any mode, not only in тАШUnilineтАЩ minor mode.  It
takes care of the infiniteness of the buffer in the right and down
directions.


