16.1 use-package, the straightforward way
=========================================

The тАШuse-packageтАЩ library became the de-facto standard to manage
packages in your тАШ.emacsтАЩ initialization file.  The тАШuse-packageтАЩ
library comes along with Emacs.  It can (among other services) delay
loading external packages until they are used, and bind keyboard
shortcuts to the packageтАЩs entry points.

   Add the following lines to your тАШ.emacsтАЩ file, and reload it, if not
already done.  This says that the popular Melpa repository is one of the
central store of third parties packages.  To day, it provides almost
7000 packages to choose from.

     (add-to-list 'package-archives
                  '("melpa" . "http://melpa.org/packages/")
                  t)
     (package-initialize)

   Alternately you may customize this variable:

     M-x customize-variable package-archives

   Then add those lines in your Emacs initialization file (usually
тАШ~/.emacsтАЩ):

     (use-package uniline-hydra
       :bind ("C-<insert>" . uniline-mode))

   or:

     (use-package uniline-transient
       :bind ("C-<insert>" . uniline-mode))

   This tell Emacs:
   тАв Be prepared to load тАШuniline-modeтАЩ when the user request it, but do
     not load it now.
   тАв Bind the тАШC-<insert>тАЩ keys to the function тАШuniline-modeтАЩ.  This
     shortens the longer тАШM-x uniline-modeтАЩ command.  Any other key
     combinations can be bound, as you prefer.  тАШ<insert>тАЩ happens to
     also be the key used inside тАШUnilineтАЩ (customizable).
   тАв Load either the тАШuniline-hydraтАЩ or the тАШuniline-transientтАЩ file, as
     you prefer.  This gives Uniline one or the other flavour of
     user-interface.

   There is an alias to тАШuniline-hydraтАЩ:

     (use-package uniline
       :bind ("C-<insert>" . uniline-mode))

   If you are using *note straight.el:: with тАШuse-packageтАЩ, and have
тАШ(setq straight-use-package-by-default t)тАЩ, you have the following
options:

     ;; uniline-hydra using the alias
     (use-package uniline)

     ;;; uniline-hydra explicitly requested
     (use-package uniline-hydra
       :straight uniline)

     ;;; install and load uniline-transient
     (use-package uniline-transient
       :straight uniline)


